  "prompt": "I'm doing my master's in information systems at the University of Washington. I have 3.5 years of experience in the Indian IT industry. I want to become a program manager at Microsoft/Google, etc. What is some advice on how I should prepare?",
  "response": "Here are some strategic steps to prepare for a Program Manager role at top tech companies:\n\nTechnical Skills:\n- Master core technical concepts\n- Learn Azure/AWS cloud platforms\n- Develop basic coding skills (Python, JavaScript)\n- Understand system design principles\n- Study agile/scrum methodologies\n\nProfessional Development:\n- Build a strong LinkedIn profile\n- Network with current Microsoft/Google program managers\n- Attend tech conferences\n- Pursue relevant certifications\n- Practice technical and behavioral interviewing\n\nAcademic Approach:\n- Take project management courses\n- Choose electives focused on product/program management\n- Work on complex group projects\n- Seek internships in PM roles\n\nResume/Experience Enhancement:\n- Highlight leadership experiences from current IT role\n- Quantify achievements with metrics\n- Showcase cross-functional collaboration\n- Develop case studies from your work experience\n\nInterview Preparation:\n- Practice PM-specific interview questions\n- Study interview formats at target companies\n- Use resources like \"Cracking the PM Interview\"\n- Do mock interviews\n- Build a portfolio demonstrating problem-solving skills\n\nAdditional Recommendations:\n- Join UW's PM student groups\n- Connect with alumni in target roles\n- Consider Microsoft/Google internship programs\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these points?",
